node.text: Covid-19 cases have been on the rise in much of the US, and the seven-day average of new cases Monday was more than 300% higher than Labor Day of last year, according to data from Johns Hopkins University. Currently, 62% of eligible Americans are fully vaccinated, leaving tens of millions very vulnerable.⁠

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 07, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, people standing, outdoors and text that says 'A statue of Christopher Columbus in Mexico City will be replaced by one of an Indigenous woman Bonos Ahoro Û ව A CNN'.

node.text:
A famous statue of Christopher Columbus in Mexico City will soon be replaced by a sculpture of an Indigenous woman, Mexico City officials announced. The Columbus statue was removed last year for restoration purposes — and to reconsider Columbus' legacy.⁠
⁠
"It's very important to dedicate a monument to indigenous women and to the Earth, because if anyone can teach us how to take care of this planet, it's our native peoples, and that is precisely what we must learn again," sculptor Pedro Reyes said, according to Mexican newspaper El Universal.⁠
⁠
(📸: AP Photo/Claudio Cruz)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 07, 2021. May be art of 1 person and indoor.

node.text:
African art is now selling for record-breaking amounts around the world.

Ivorian rising star Abdoulaye Diarrassouba, better known as Aboudia, sold "Untitled (2015)" for $232,000, a whopping 835% over presale valuation estimates and shattering his personal record set last year.

Renowned Nigerian artist Ben Enwonwu's "Atlas" sold for over half a million dollars at a Sotheby's auction in March, setting a new world record for an African sculpture.

For more, follow @cnnstyle.

(📸: John Phillips/Getty Images for Sotheby's, Sia Kambou/AFP/Getty Images and Ben Enwonwu/Sotheby's)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 06, 2021. May be an image of sky and text that says 'A former Walmart executive wants to build a $400 billion city in the American desert TAL CNN'.

node.text:
Billionaire Marc Lore, a former Walmart executive, unveiled his plans for Telosa, a sustainable metropolis that he hopes to create, from scratch, in the American desert. The ambitious 150,000-acre proposal would house 5 million people. Although planners are still scouting for locations, possible targets include Nevada, Utah, Idaho, Arizona, Texas and the Appalachian region, according to the project's official website.⁠
⁠
(📸: Bjarke Ingels Group)

node.text:

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 06, 2021. May be an image of ‎2 people, child and ‎text that says '‎Twins joined at the head are separated after 12-hour surgery The girls can now face each other for the first time since they were born a year ago CLLIU CNN רכ×¨××‎'‎‎.

node.text:
One-year-old Israeli twin girls, who were born joined back-to-back at the head, have been separated after a rare and complicated surgery. Conjoined twins occur once every 200,000 live births, according to the University of Minnesota. They are always identical and most are female.⁠
⁠
(📸: Soroka Medical Centre/Reuters)

Here's what we know: Bryan Riley, 33, broke into two homes outside Lakeland, Florida, early Sunday morning. Four people were killed in the shooting, including a 3-month-old baby, according to authorities. He had no clear motive, and there are no apparent connections between the suspect and the four victims. Riley now faces four counts of first-degree murder and charges of attempted murder, arson and armed burglary. "We just know we had a madman with a lot of guns that shot and killed innocent people," Sheriff Grady Judd said.'.

node.text:
A former Marine who told his girlfriend he was receiving visions from God broke into two homes outside Lakeland, Florida, on Sunday and fatally shot four people, including a 3-month-old baby, according to authorities.⁠
⁠
(📸: Polk County Sheriff/Twitter)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 06, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Doctors in some US states could soon be forced to make tough choices about who gets an ICU bed, Dr. Anthony Fauci warns CNN'.

node.text: Across the US, 79.8% of ICU beds are in use — and almost a third are occupied by Covid-19 patients, according to data from the US Department of Health and Human Services. Eight states had more than 90% of their adult ICU beds occupied Sunday: Alabama, Georgia, Texas, Arkansas, Florida, Mississippi, Nevada and Kentucky.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 06, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, outdoors and text.

node.text:
The US Military Academy at West Point will finally unveil a new monument dedicated to the Buffalo Soldiers, a group of Black soldiers who played a key role in the westward expansion of the US. The Buffalo Soldiers taught riding skills at the academy for 40 years.⁠
⁠
"This monument will ensure that the legacy of Buffalo Soldiers is enduringly revered, honored and celebrated while serving as an inspiration for the next generations of cadets," said US Military Academy 60th Superintendent, Lt. Gen. Darryl A. Williams.⁠
⁠
(📸: Jackie Molloy/ The Washington Post/Getty Images)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on September 05, 2021. May be an image of chandelier and text that says 'Nurse transforms Covid vaccine vials into a chandelier to honor health care workers CNN'.

node.text:
A nurse in Colorado took empty Covid-19 vaccine vials and made them into beautiful art, paying tribute to her fellow health care workers. "I had noticed all these hundreds and hundreds of empty vaccine vials that were otherwise going to be wasted, and I thought they were just really beautiful and wanted to do something significant and meaningful with them," nurse Laura Weiss said.⁠
⁠
(📸: Laura Weiss)
